________________________________________
23️⃣ Privileged Access Management (PAM)
________________________________________

🧭 Overview
PAM isolates privileged accounts and limits their scope, time of use, and exposure.

🏗️ Implementation Steps
1.	Deploy Microsoft Identity Manager (MIM) with PAM components.
2.	Set up bastion forest with limited trust to the production domain.
3.	Configure shadow principals, time-limited group membership, and access workflows.

🔒 Key Features
•	Just-In-Time (JIT) access
•	Time-bound group membership
•	Shadow security principals
•	Workflow approvals

🧠 Use New-PAMUser and Add-PAMUserToRole PowerShell cmdlets for automation.
________________________________________
🧊 24️⃣ Read-Only Domain Controllers (RODCs)
________________________________________

💡 Use Case
•	Branch offices or locations with low physical security.

🛠️ Deployment Steps
1.	Add a new domain controller using Server Manager or PowerShell.
2.	On the Deployment Configuration, select Read-only domain controller.
3.	Set replication source domain controller.
4.	Configure Password Replication Policy (PRP):
o	Allow: Users/groups that can cache credentials.
o	Deny: High-privilege accounts (Domain Admins).

🔐 Security Advantages
•	No write access to AD database.
•	Mitigates risk in untrusted environments.
•	Credential caching is selective and controlled.

🔎 Use Get-ADDomainController -Filter * | Where-Object { $_.IsReadOnly } to list RODCs.
________________________________________
🧬 25️⃣ AD Schema Extension & Custom Attributes
________________________________________

📦 Extending the Schema
Use ldifde to import new schema definitions:
ldifde -i -f customattribute.ldf -k -j .
Example LDIF snippet:
dn: CN=Custom-Attribute,CN=Schema,CN=Configuration,DC=vlab,DC=local
changetype: add
adminDisplayName: CustomAttribute
attributeID: 1.2.840.113556.1.8000.999999.1
attributeSyntax: 2.5.5.12
isSingleValued: TRUE
objectClass: attributeSchema

🔧 Use Cases
•	Add employeeID, officeLocation, or customAccessLevel to user objects.

🔍 PowerShell Management
Set-ADUser -Identity john.doe -Add @{extensionAttribute15="Level3"}
Get-ADUser -Filter * -Properties extensionAttribute15

🧠 Always back up AD and test in a lab before applying schema changes.

